post_text:
Hello LPPS Community:

Just some insight to help clarify the food distribution process. Any Lincoln Park family can pre-order the meals for all of their students using the www.mypaymentsplus.com website or the app. All pre-orders must be made by Noon on Tuesdays. You can then pick these items up at whatever school you choose in your pre-order. If you do not pre-order, you can drop in on the high school site and pick up your meals there. Unfortunately, you cannot just drop in to the elementary sites, you will need to pre-order for that. Also, we were aware that there was a problem with the app and that has now been resolved. More information regarding the meal distribution can be found on our site. www.lincolnparkpublicschools.com/returntolearn

Foote Elementary School
September 5 at 11:28 AM ·

Wednesday, September 9th is the 1st day of school. All students will have a 9:00 AM Class Meeting.

We encourage you to make sure you can get logged on using the Clever badge you were given in your welcome packet. When you log-in, it may show last year's teacher but this will be updated by Wednesday.

If you have any difficulties, please call the Foote office on Tuesday between 8:30 AM and 2:30 PM so we can fix any issues prior to the Wednesday morning meetings.

If you did not pick up your Chromebook or welcome packet, please call the Foote office on Tuesday to arrange a pick-up time.

We cannot wait to begin the new school year with you!

shared_text:
Lincoln Park Middle School
September 8 at 12:03 PM ·

Good Morning LPMS Families! Tomorrow, September 9th, is the first day of school! We are excited to see you all, even though it will be virtually. Remember, there are no in-person classes tomorrow at LPMS.

On Wednesday, students will follow the Half Day Bell Schedule. Thursday, September 10th, students will follow the Full Day Bell Schedule.

Please be sure to log in to Student/Parent Connect before tomorrow to check your schedule. If you need assistance, please call the Main Office.

By the end of the day today, you will have received an email from each of your teachers with their Google Meet Link. Please join each Google Meet tomorrow for each class period, as though you were following your regular schedule in school!

We are excited to work together this year, be flexible, stay positive, and do our best in true Railsplitter fashion!

post_text:
Hello LPPS Families:

I just wanted to take a moment and thank everyone that participated in our Chromebook distribution this past week. After 4 consecutive days we distributed 4060 Chromebooks! It was a difficult task and at times we faced huge crowds and moments of zero people in line. We faced some people getting in line hours before we opened to people arriving just as we were closing. Through it all, we saw smiling faces, LP pride, and a task complete. Thank you to our Director of Technology Mr. Ken Jacobs for planning all of this and to all our countless staff members that worked tirelessly to ensure we got out as many of these devices as we could. For those that could not get a Chromebook this week, you can do that next week through your child's school office.

Have a great weekend!

Terry Dangerfield
Superintendent

Governor Gretchen Whitmer
June 30 at 10:15 PM ·

Today, I signed an executive order and released the MI Safe Schools Roadmap to provide a structure to support schools in Michigan as they plan for a return of K-12 education this fall. The executive order and the MI Safe Schools Roadmap are available at Michigan.gov/Coronavirus.

‪Our educators and parents have shown extraordinary leadership during the COVID-19 pandemic. While there are unknowns about the future of COVID-19 in Michigan, this plan provides the guidance, support, and clarity that is needed to safely bring students back to the classroom.‬

‪What the upcoming school year will be like for our kids depends on each of us doing our part to flatten the COVID-19 curve. Please, continue to stay smart, stay safe, and take every recommended precaution so that our children can be safe in their classrooms this fall.‬

shared_text:
City of Lincoln Park
June 9 at 4:58 PM ·

Gleaners Community Food Bank has partnered with the City of Lincoln Park to schedule a drive up food distribution event on Thursday, June 18 at 2:00pm at LP Community Center (3525 Dix Highway)

HELPING OUR COMMUNITY DURING URGENT TIMES OF NEED
Families and individuals in need of food are encouraged to attend an upcoming drive-up distribution provided by Gleaners Community Food Bank.

~30 pounds of groceries—Items like milk, fresh fruits, vegetables, lean protein and other shelf-stable items.

Drive-up or walk-up—Stay in your vehicle, and groceries will be placed into your trunk. Walk up guests without vehicles or those without a trunk are welcome to obtain groceries from a self-service table. If walking, please be prepared to carry the groceries or have a cart.

No appointment needed—You do not need to bring identification or proof of eligibility to receive food.

Increasing safety— If you wish to pick up for another household you may do so without their presence in the car.

Foote Elementary School
June 1 at 5:49 PM ·

We are now enrolling our future kindergarten students at Foote Elementary School!

Here is the link for our online pre-enrollment: https://sisweb.resa.net/LincolnPark/PreEnrollment

Simply click this link and the directions will walk you through step by step. Please note, if you are not a resident of Lincoln Park, you must fill out the School of Choice Application located on the very first page of pre-enrollment link.

If there is anything I can do to help you, please do not hesitate to contact me at kelly.reynolds@lpps.info. Our school secretary, Mrs. Soyko, would be happy to help answer any enrollment questions. Please reach her at teena.soyko@lpps.info.

We look forward to meeting the Class of 2033. Go Rails!

We are now enrolling our future kindergarten students at Foote Elementary School!

Here is the link for our online pre-enrollment: https://sisweb.resa.net/LincolnPark/PreEnrollment

Simply click this link and the directions will walk you through step by step. Please note, if you are not a resident of Lincoln Park, you must fill out the School of Choice Application located on the very first page of pre-enrollment link.

If there is anything I can do to help you, please do not hesitate to contact me at kelly.reynolds@lpps.info. Our school secretary, Mrs. Soyko, would be happy to help answer any enrollment questions. Please reach her at teena.soyko@lpps.info.

We look forward to meeting the Class of 2033. Go Rails!

post_text:
Happy Memorial Day! Just sending a reminder.

RE: Food Distribution

We wanted to provide an update on what our food service distribution will look like over the next few weeks.

In light of the Memorial Day holiday, food distribution will occur WEDNESDAY May 27, 2020 this week. We will return to our normal distribution on Tuesday June 2.

The current food distribution system is set to continue until June 23, 2020. How the summer food program will be distributed is still being decided based on what the recommendations from the state will be. We will keep you posted once we have more information.

Thank you Lincoln Park! Have a great night and stay safe!

shared_text:
Lincoln Park Softball
May 20 at 12:46 PM ·

Day 5 of 5 Celebrating OUR seniors is

Jenna Brewer

All District and All Region player last year, I can almost guarantee she would have been an All State player this year. You talk about pure softball player she is at the top of the list. She knows the game inside and out. Every time she stepped to the plate I knew she would see 8+ pitches, get a hit or both. It was always fun and exciting to watch her at the plate. She played multiple infield position and she played everyone well. She is continuing her Education at Trine University as a Bowler. I am so proud of her, because she is able to go to next level regardless of the sport. To her I say, “Go strike out!” Never thought you hear a softball coach say that, bowl all the 300 games you can. Show them your competitiveness and desire to win! Don’t be a stranger to the program and best of luck to you, Go Rails!

shared_text:
Lincoln Park Softball
May 19 at 12:12 PM ·

Day 4 of 5 celebrating OUR seniors is

Jade Bates

Jade Bates, Jade Bates, Jade Bates, as the team chants in the dugout! Jade is the best combination of athleticism and softball player I have ever coached. She is the player every team wants. Every coach would say, “I’d love to have that #9.” I’m grateful she was a Railsplitter. She wore that orange and blue with pride! The 5 tool player they talk about, she is just that, she can hit for a high batting average, for power, runs the bases well, throws well and fields well. She is undecided where she wants to attend school, but where ever she goes I hope she takes the opportunity to walk on to the softball team because they would get a great athlete, softball player, and most importantly a GREAT person. Jade was also an All League, All District and All New Herald player for us two years in a row(she would have done it again.) Don’t be a stranger to the program, Go Rails!

RE: Food Distribution

We wanted to provide an update on what our food service distribution will look like over the next few weeks.

In light of the Memorial Day holiday, food distribution next week will occur WEDNESDAY May 27, 2020. We will return to our normal distribution on Tuesday June 2.

The current food distribution system is set to continue until June 23, 2020. How the summer food program will be distributed is still being decided based on what the recommendations from the state will be. We will keep you posted once we have more information.

Thank you Lincoln Park! Have a great week and Memorial Day weekend. Stay safe!

The LP Rundown
May 16 at 11:01 PM ·

ATTENTION ALL LPPS FAMILIES:

We have received a notification from the MDE requesting our assistance with the distribution of the PEBT food funding cards.

1. If you have a student(s) in the Lincoln Park Public Schools (LPPS) AND;
2. you had a change of address during the 2019-2020 school year AND;
3. you have NOT received your PEBT food card THEN;

please send an email to enroll@lpps.info with the following information:

Parent/Guardian Name
Current Mailing Address
Email Address
Phone Number
Names of ALL of your children that attend the Lincoln Park Public Schools and live at this address

Please note this is ONLY for those that meet ALL 3 criteria stated above. If you have not moved OR have already received your PEBT card funds OR have already notified the school of your address change prior to May 15, 2020, you do NOT need to email the school district.

If you meet all of the 3 criteria, please complete this email by Friday, May 22, 2020.

Thank you all for your cooperation. Stay safe and stay healthy! Go Rails!

This will take place on Tuesday May 26, 2020 at 6:00 p.m. All you have to do is simply click on the link below that matches the elementary building that represents your neighborhood school or you plan to send your kindergarten child to next fall. Raupp Elementary
May 18 at 3:32 PM ·

Happy Monday!
I miss you all and hope you are staying active and motivated to stay healthy! Attached is a video of one of my students that created an obstacle course using sidewalk chalk! I am so proud of his dedication to staying healthy and active. I am challenging you to create an obstacle course of your own or using the following example:

https://handsonaswegrow.com/super-simple-sidewalk-chalk-gross-motor-obstacle-course/

I really liked this example because it gives you ways to use sight words, verbs, letter recognition, and you could even use multiplication problems or other math problems for older students.
Keep smiling, Mrs. Murray

ATTENTION ALL LPPS FAMILIES:

We have received a notification from the MDE requesting our assistance with the distribution of the PEBT food funding cards.

1. If you have a student(s) in the Lincoln Park Public Schools (LPPS) AND;
2. you had a change of address during the 2019-2020 school year AND;
3. you have NOT received your PEBT food card THEN;

please send an email to enroll@lpps.info with the following information:

Parent/Guardian Name
Current Mailing Address
Email Address
Phone Number
Names of ALL of your children that attend the Lincoln Park Public Schools and live at this address

Please note this is ONLY for those that meet ALL 3 criteria stated above. If you have not moved OR have already received your PEBT card funds OR have already notified the school of your address change prior to May 15, 2020, you do NOT need to email the school district.

If you meet all of the 3 criteria, please complete this email by Friday, May 22, 2020.

Thank you all for your cooperation. Stay safe and stay healthy! Go Rails!

Mrs. Cooper's STEM Lab
May 15 at 2:35 PM ·

FLASHBACK FRIDAY!!!!

Back in October, I brought my Milkweed plants to the classroom for the winter! Boy we were in for a surprise! We had some late Monarch eggs! The students were able to witness the entire transformation of the monarch butterfly! It wasn’t too interesting at first, but once the caterpillars started to get big, the students couldn’t wait to see how they would change from day to day! What an awesome experience for them!!!!
